    "note": "GA4 native conversions are effectively unconfigured: lead events (form_submit, click_phone_number, click_email) and the gmb_click event fire but are not flagged as key events/conversions, so GA4 reports ~0 conversions. The dashboards now split these into two series: Generated leads (form_submit + click_phone_number + click_email + contact_form_submit) and GBP clicks (gmb_click), since GBP clicks measure interest in the listing rather than completed leads. click_phone_number and click_email tagging only went live in April 2026, so a portion of the Q1->Q2 jump is instrumentation, not demand. Configuring the lead events as key events in GA4 is a P0 (same gap seen on Professional Movers)."
